  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-8 clean, bounded envelope)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Operating envelope is explicitly bounded: flow rates 1–7 L/min, rotational speeds 2000–5000 RPM, hematocrit 35–45%, inlet temperature 36–38 °C, and impeller tip clearance within ±0.05 mm of nominal. Validation samples span 8 of 35 envelope cells; coverage gaps are documented but do not preclude acceptance at the assessed operating points. All 13 credibility factors are assessed with achieved levels meeting or exceeding required levels. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification performed on all five hemolysis QoIs. Decision: Accepted for the bounded operating envelope with documented coverage constraints.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Low",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/morrison/req/cou2-hemolysis-absolute-threshold",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/cou2-cfd-hemolysis-credible-bounded-envelope",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/morrison/model/cfd-centrifugal-pump-hemolysis-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/fda-pump-hemolysis-experimental-v2",
    "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/fda-pump-cfd-mesh-convergence-study",
    "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/monte-carlo-uq-hemolysis-5qoi"
  ],
  "hasContextOfUse": "{\"id\": \"https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou2-vad\", \"type\": \"ContextOfUse\", \"name\": \"COU2: Ventricular assist device use (Class III)\", \"description\": \"A CFD model is used to predict absolute hemolysis levels across operating conditions for a centrifugal blood pump used as a ventricular assist device (VAD). Model influence is HIGH (model is primary basis for hemolysis acceptance); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect prediction could result in chronic patient hemolysis requiring clinical intervention). Model Risk Level 5 — the highest in the Morrison assessment.\", \"deviceClass\": \"Class III\", \"modelInfluence\": \"High\", \"decisionConsequence\": \"High\", \"intendedUse\": \"Use CFD to predict absolute hemolysis index values for a Class III VAD device across 5 flow-speed combinations. Results must demonstrate hemolysis below absolute clinical threshold (not relative to predicate). Requires Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification on hemolysis predictions.\", \"hasApplicabilityConstraint\": {\"id\": \"https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou2-vad/applicability-constraint\", \"type\": \"ApplicabilityConstraint\", \"name\": \"COU2 applicability constraint: centrifugal VAD hemolysis domain\", \"description\": \"Model applicability is restricted to single-stage centrifugal blood pumps with impeller diameter 50–70 mm, operating with human whole blood (hematocrit 35–45%), at physiological temperature (36–38 °C), and inlet pressures 5–20 mmHg. Axial pumps, pulsatile flow devices, and blood analogue fluids are explicitly out of scope. The Giersiepen–Wurzinger power-law hemolysis correlation is applicable only within the shear-stress range 1–600 Pa and exposure times 0.001–1 s as validated against the Morrison dataset.\"}, \"hasOperatingEnvelope\": {\"id\": \"https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou2-vad/operating-envelope\", \"type\": \"OperatingEnvelope\", \"name\": \"COU2 operating envelope: bounded flow-speed-geometry space\", \"description\": \"Bounded operating envelope: volumetric flow rate 1–7 L/min (increment 1 L/min), rotational speed 2000–5000 RPM (increment 500 RPM), hematocrit 35–45% (nominal 40%), inlet fluid temperature 36–38 °C, impeller tip clearance 0.25 mm ± 0.05 mm, outlet pressure 60–120 mmHg. Validation experiments sampled 8 cells of the 35-cell flow-speed grid (flow rates 2, 4, 6 L/min × speeds 2500, 3000, 4000 RPM plus two additional corner points); remaining 27 cells rely on interpolated CFD predictions with documented uncertainty bounds. Operation outside these bounds is not covered by this UofA.\"}}}",
