        "description": "Selection of the SST k-ω turbulence model and Giersiepen–Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model must be justified by published benchmark comparisons against the FDA pump dataset and sensitivity analysis demonstrating that alternative turbulence models (k-ε realizable, LES) change NIH predictions by less than 15% within the bounded envelope. Achieved: sensitivity analysis documented in SA-MFORM-2024 report; maximum NIH change across turbulence model variants = 11.3%."
