        "description": "All uncertain model inputs (blood viscosity, density, Casson model parameters, pump geometry tolerances, inlet velocity profile) must have documented probability distributions derived from literature or measurement, and Monte Carlo propagation (N ≥ 1000 samples) must yield 95th-percentile NIH predictions below the clinical threshold. Achieved: 2000-sample Monte Carlo study documented in UQ-MC-2024 report; 95th-percentile NIH = 0.0034 g/100 L (threshold 0.008 g/100 L)."
